==Hindi==
===Demonstrative pronoun===
'''इन''' (in)

# [[these]] - [[oblique]] case only, see below for direct. (Singular: [[इस]])
#:Example: "इन मकानों [[में]] [[छह]] कमरे हैं" - "In these houses there are six rooms." Literally - "These houses in six rooms are."
# [[him]] - oblique case only, near reference, polite. (If no additional [[respect]] is conveyed, [[इस]] is used)
#:Example: "इनको [[पैसे]] [[देना|दे]] [[दो]]" - Give money to him. Literally "Him to money give."
# [[her]] - oblique case only, near reference. (If no additional [[respect]] is conveyed, इस is used)
#:Example "इनको पैसे दे दो" - Give money to her. (The same)
# [[it]] - oblique case only.
#:Example "इन [[लेना|लो]]" - Take these.

====Inflection====
[[Direct]]: [[ये]]

===See also===
*[[उन]](un) - [[Those]], [[him]] and [[her]] (far reference).

